http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/tamil-nadu/Hostel-inmates-demand-basic-amenities/article14024084.ece

More than 130 inmates, mostly students of Mother Teresa University, of a girls’ hostel run by the Department of Backward Classes and Minorities Welfare at Attuvampatti, blocked Kodaikanal-Pallangi Road here on Wednesday morning, condemning lack of basic amenities in the hostel and supply of poor quality food.Five students fainted as food was not served to them for the past two days in the hostel, alleged the university students. Traffic was disrupted for more than an hour.With no water supply in the hostel for the past two months, students had to depend on a public tap. “We had tough time at night hours,” they added.'Food was not prepared properly in the hostel. The food prepared in the morning was served to them in the afternoon and at night as well. The warden did not stay in the hostel and visited the place rarely. The hostel cook was the sole in-charge of the place, they said.When the inmates lodged a complaint with authorities concerned, the warden threatened them and even went to the extent of assaulting them, the students alleged.The food prepared in the morning was served to them in the afternoon and at night as well